message.content: A 'Papilio zelicaon' is a species of butterfly commonly referred to as the Anise Swallowtail. The butterfly is predominantly black with a striking yellow band and rows of blue spots on its wings. Its wingspan can range from 2.75 to 4 inches. The Anise Swallowtail has a sleek and slender body with long antennae. You can find this species in various habitats including gardens, parks, and open woodland. The butterfly feeds on the nectar of flowers, particularly ones within the Apiaceae family. The Anise Swallowtail is native to western North America, spanning from British Columbia to Northern Mexico.
